	(text "U3 is just anlog inputs with resistor dividers. Both ADCs VDD is 3.3v which means max\ninput on AIN0,1,2,3 is 3.3v. So the resistor dividers allow for up to 5v. \n\nU4 AIN0 and AIN1 are regular singled ended inputs just like U3. Up to 5v.\nHowever, AIN2 and AIN3 are inputs for thermistors. The 100k resistors are the \ntop half of a divider and the thermister is the bottom half. Assuming a thermistor\nthat is 100k at 25C with a Beta of 3950. \n\nThe ALERT/READY pins go to the ESP32 to trigger interrupts. This design assumes the\nconfig register of the ADS1115 will be set to continous mode and the LSB and MSB bits\nof the high and low threshold registers will be configured to enable secondary mode\nof the ALERT READY pin. This results in a pulse every time a reading is ready.\nRead the datasheet. \n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 78.105 179.705 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "0cf802be-dfe7-4696-bfbe-bc9e76aa6238")
	)
